DAYID.description: Ngày dữ liệu. Represents the date of the data record. All records in this sample pertain to the same date.
DAYID.domain: Represents a specific date. In this dataset, it's a constant 2025-03-25.
DAYID.constraints_description: Must be a valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. All records are from 2025-03-25.
DAYID.relationships: This likely relates to when the account information was snapshotted or the transaction recorded.
DAYID.data_quality: Verify date format (YYYY-MM-DD). Ensure date is consistent across all records if that's the expected behavior.

CONTRACT.description: Mã tài khoản (mã quản lý hệ thống). Unique identifier for the bank account, managed by the system.
CONTRACT.domain: A unique account identifier with a length between 12 and 13 digits.
CONTRACT.constraints_description: Must be a numeric string with a length between 12 and 13. Must be unique.
CONTRACT.relationships: This is the central identifier that likely connects to other tables related to account details, transactions, customer information, etc.
CONTRACT.data_quality: Validate length (12-13 digits). Ensure uniqueness. Check for valid numeric characters only.

DATASOURCE.description: Nguồn dữ liệu. Identifies the source of the account data. AZ, MM: Term deposits including savings, deposit contracts, certificates of deposit, bonds. LD: Savings with interest paid in advance. SC: Installment savings.
DATASOURCE.domain: Categorical values representing the source of the data (AZ, MM, LD, SC).
DATASOURCE.constraints_description: Must be one of the valid data source codes: AZ, MM, LD, SC.
DATASOURCE.relationships: This column may influence interest rates or account types. Connects to business rules or account configurations.
DATASOURCE.data_quality: Verify the allowed values are from the list (AZ, MM, LD, SC). Handle nulls according to the business rules (e.g. impute or filter).

CHANNEL_NAME.description: Kênh giao dịch. Specifies the channel through which the transaction or interaction occurred (e.g., Branch, Internet Banking).
CHANNEL_NAME.domain: Categorical values representing the channel (BRANCH, SEANET, PHOIAO, ARCIB).
CHANNEL_NAME.constraints_description: Must be one of the allowed channel names: BRANCH, SEANET, PHOIAO, ARCIB.
CHANNEL_NAME.relationships: This can be related to geographic location or customer segment, or even service type.
CHANNEL_NAME.data_quality: Validate allowed values. Address missing values appropriately. Could be correlated with transaction amounts.

CO_CODE.description: Mã phòng giao dịch . Represents the code of the transaction office (branch).
CO_CODE.domain: A code identifying the specific branch or transaction office. Format is typically VN followed by digits.
CO_CODE.constraints_description: Starts with VN and followed by digits. Length should be consistent across all values. Must refer to a valid branch code.
CO_CODE.relationships: Relates to customer demographics, transaction volume, and potentially channel information.
CO_CODE.data_quality: Ensure all values start with VN. Check that the codes are valid against a reference table of branch codes.  Validate length and character set.

CATEGORY.description: Mã category của hợp đồng tiền gửi. This represents the type or classification of the deposit account agreement, influencing its features, interest rates, and applicable regulations.  Examples include current accounts, savings accounts, fixed deposit accounts, or specialized accounts like student or senior citizen accounts.  Understanding the category is crucial for risk assessment and product targeting.
CATEGORY.domain: A set of predefined integer codes representing different account categories offered by the bank (e.g., 6515: Savings Account, 6537: Current Account, etc.).
CATEGORY.constraints_description: The CATEGORY codes should belong to a predefined list of valid categories managed by SeABank.  This ensures data integrity and consistency.
CATEGORY.relationships: Strong functional dependency with CATEGORY_SK, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK implying these are all linked to this category.
CATEGORY.data_quality: Verify that all CATEGORY codes are present in a reference table. Monitor the distribution of categories over time for unusual shifts. Important to confirm its relation to other foreign keys such as the AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, CUSTOMER_SK, SEAB_LOS_ID, etc.

CUSTOMER.description: Mã khách hàng. This represents the unique identifier for each customer of the bank. It is used to track customer information, transaction history, and relationship with the bank. A proper customer ID is crucial for regulatory compliance (KYC) and fraud detection.
CUSTOMER.domain: Integer values representing the unique identifier for each customer.  Range should fall within the defined customer ID range within the bank's system.
CUSTOMER.constraints_description: CUSTOMER IDs should be unique within the entire database. A specific prefix or range might be used for different customer segments.
CUSTOMER.relationships: Strong functional dependency with CUSTOMER_SK, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK suggesting they are all dependent on the customer.
CUSTOMER.data_quality: Check for duplicates in CUSTOMER IDs. Cross-validate with other customer-related tables to ensure consistency of customer information.  Verify if it is a valid foreign key for the customer dimension/table.

PRODUCT_CODE.description: Mã sản phẩm SeABank theo cây Product. This identifies the specific banking product that a customer has subscribed to (e.g., a particular type of loan, savings account, or credit card). This is vital for understanding the bank's product portfolio, sales performance, and customer preferences.
PRODUCT_CODE.domain: Integer codes representing the specific banking product. The range is defined by the bank's internal product catalog.
PRODUCT_CODE.constraints_description: The PRODUCT_CODE should correspond to a valid and active product within the SeABank product portfolio. Check against a product reference table.
PRODUCT_CODE.relationships: High correlation with PRODUCTS_SK, suggesting a parent-child relationship. A functional dependency exists between PRODUCT_CODE, PRODUCTS_SK, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
PRODUCT_CODE.data_quality: Verify the existence of each PRODUCT_CODE in a master product list. Analyze the distribution of product codes and identify any discontinued products. Check PRODUCTS_SK and CLOSE_REASON match the current database.

CURRENCY.description: Loại tiền tệ của tài khoản. The currency in which the account balance is maintained. This is critical for financial reporting, exchange rate calculations, and international transactions.
CURRENCY.domain: A standardized currency code (e.g., VND, USD, EUR).
CURRENCY.constraints_description: The CURRENCY should be a valid ISO 4217 currency code.  The values VND (Vietnamese Dong) and USD (US Dollar) are the only acceptable ones based on the stats
CURRENCY.relationships: The currency influences the values in balance-related columns (CLOSE_BAL, OPEN_BAL, etc.).
CURRENCY.data_quality: Validate against a list of valid currency codes. Investigate accounts with currencies other than VND, as the data suggests this is highly unusual. If a valid currency code is provided, ensure that corresponding exchange rates are correctly applied in any currency conversions.

CLOSE_BAL.description: Số dư cuối ngày (trước cob). The closing balance of the account at the end of the day. This is a key metric for tracking account activity and financial performance.
CLOSE_BAL.domain: Numeric value representing the account balance in the account currency. The valid range is non-negative, reflecting the permissible account balance range in VND or USD.
CLOSE_BAL.constraints_description: The CLOSE_BAL should be a non-negative number. Check for outliers exceeding reasonable limits based on account type and customer profile.
CLOSE_BAL.relationships: Strong positive correlations with CLOSE_BAL_LCY, AGG_BAL_MTD, AGG_BAL_YTD, WORKING_BALANCE, indicating these balances tend to move together. A functional dependency exists between CLOSE_BAL, CLOSE_BAL_LCY, CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
CLOSE_BAL.data_quality: Validate that the CLOSE_BAL is not negative. Compare the CLOSE_BAL with the OPEN_BAL to identify significant fluctuations.  Ensure that CLOSE_BAL_LCY represents the same value as CLOSE_BAL expressed in local currency. Investigate large discrepancies with other balance fields. Given the functional dependency with other fields, double check to ensure their data quality as well.

CLOSE_BAL_LCY.description: Số dư cuối ngày (trước cob) quy đổi VNĐ. This represents the closing balance of an account in Vietnamese Dong (VND) after currency conversion, prior to the end-of-day batch processing.
CLOSE_BAL_LCY.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Represents a valid VND amount.

validation_rules: Check for outliers beyond the statistical range.
Verify consistency with associated account balances (e.g., WORKING_BALANCE).
Perform currency validation to ensure it is in VND.

AGG_BAL_MTD.description: Tổng số dư Close_Bal từ đầu tháng tới dayid. This represents the aggregate sum of the closing balances from the beginning of the month up to the current day.
AGG_BAL_MTD.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Cannot exceed the AGG_BAL_YTD value. Represents a valid VND amount.

validation_rules: Should be less than or equal to AGG_BAL_YTD.
Check for outliers beyond the statistical range.
Verify consistency with associated account balances (e.g., WORKING_BALANCE).

AGG_BAL_MTD_LCY.description: Tổng số dư Close_Bal từ đầu tháng tới dayid quy đổi. This represents the aggregate sum of the closing balances from the beginning of the month up to the current day, converted to Vietnamese Dong (VND).
AGG_BAL_MTD_LCY.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Cannot exceed the AGG_BAL_YTD_LCY value. Represents a valid VND amount.

validation_rules: Should be less than or equal to AGG_BAL_YTD_LCY.
Check for outliers beyond the statistical range.
Verify consistency with associated account balances (e.g., WORKING_BALANCE).

AGG_BAL_YTD.description: Tổng số dư close_bal từ đầu năm tới dayid. This represents the aggregate sum of the closing balances from the beginning of the year up to the current day.
AGG_BAL_YTD.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Represents a valid VND amount.

validation_rules: Check for outliers beyond the statistical range.
Verify consistency with associated account balances (e.g., WORKING_BALANCE).

AGG_BAL_YTD_LCY.description: Tổng số dư close_bal từ đầu năm tới dayid quy đổi ra VNĐ. This represents the aggregate sum of the closing balances from the beginning of the year up to the current day, converted to Vietnamese Dong (VND).
AGG_BAL_YTD_LCY.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Represents a valid VND amount.

validation_rules: Check for outliers beyond the statistical range.
Verify consistency with associated account balances (e.g., WORKING_BALANCE).

AGG_BAL.description: Tổng số dư lũy kế từ khi mở tài khoản tới dayid. This represents the cumulative balance of the account from its opening date to the current day.
AGG_BAL.domain: Values represent the total balance and should fall within a reasonable range for personal or business accounts, e.g., 0 to 1,000,000,000,000 VND.
AGG_BAL.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number.  Should be consistent with transaction history.
AGG_BAL.relationships: Positively correlated with ACCR_REMAIN and FIRST_BALANCE. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
AGG_BAL.data_quality: Check for outliers. Verify consistency with transaction history and account opening balance. Should never be negative.

TOT_INTEREST_AMT.description: Total interest amount. Total amount of interest paid on the account
TOT_INTEREST_AMT.domain: Values represent the total interest amount and should fall within a reasonable range, e.g., 0 to 100,000,000 VND.
TOT_INTEREST_AMT.relationships: Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
TOT_INTEREST_AMT.data_quality: Check for outliers. Verify consistency with interest rates and account balances. Should never be negative.

REVAL_RATE.description: Tỷ giá cuối ngày. The exchange rate at the end of the day.
REVAL_RATE.domain: Values represent the revaluation rate and should be either 1.0 (for VND) or around 23,000-26,000 (for USD/VND).
REVAL_RATE.constraints_description: Should be a valid exchange rate for the currency. Should typically be close to the official exchange rate.
REVAL_RATE.relationships: Positively correlated and functionally dependent on CURRENCY_SK. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
REVAL_RATE.data_quality: Check for valid exchange rates. Ensure consistency with the currency code. Should correspond to publicly available exchange rates for the given date.

INTEREST_RATE.description: Lãi suất hợp đồng. The contract interest rate.
INTEREST_RATE.domain: Values represent the interest rate and should fall within a realistic range for loan or deposit products, e.g., 0% to 12%.
INTEREST_RATE.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Should be consistent with the type of account. Typically between 0% and 12%.
INTEREST_RATE.relationships: Positively correlated with ORIG_INTEREST_RATE, OFFER_RATE, and FIRST_INTEREST. Functionally dependent on REVAL_RATE, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, and CURRENCY_SK.
INTEREST_RATE.data_quality: Check for valid interest rates. Ensure consistency with the type of product and prevailing market rates. Should not be negative.

ACCR_INT.description: Tổng số tiền lãi dự chi đến ngày DAYID của kỳ lãi hiện tại. Total accrued interest up to DAYID for the current interest period.
ACCR_INT.domain: Values represent the accrued interest and should fall within a reasonable range based on the account balance and interest rate, e.g., 0 to 1,000,000,000 VND.
ACCR_INT.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Should be consistent with the account balance and interest rate. Accrued interest should not exceed a reasonable amount based on the interest rate and the time period.
ACCR_INT.relationships: Positively correlated with ACCR_REMAIN, WORKING_BALANCE, ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL, OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL, and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
ACCR_INT.data_quality: Check for outliers. Verify consistency with account balance, interest rate, and the time period. Should never be negative.

ACCR_REMAIN.description: Accrued Interest Remaining: The amount of interest that has accumulated on an account but has not yet been paid out. This represents the bank's liability to the account holder for the interest earned. It includes both positive and negative values (potentially indicating reversed or corrected accruals).
ACCR_REMAIN.domain: Values range from -250,033,974 to 59,432,547,945 VND. Typically positive, but can be negative due to accrual corrections. Reflects the accrued interest due to the account holder.
ACCR_REMAIN.constraints_description: Must be a numeric value. Values should be within the observed min and max. Significant deviations from the mean and median (e.g., exceeding 3 standard deviations) should be flagged for review.
ACCR_REMAIN.relationships: Strong positive correlation with WORKING_BALANCE, ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL, OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL, and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK
ACCR_REMAIN.data_quality: Validate values are within the observed range. Check for large deviations from the mean. Impute missing values carefully, potentially using the median or mean based on the distribution within similar account segments.

REMAIN_TERM.description: Remaining Term: The remaining term of a deposit or loan, expressed in months (M) or days (D). D00 indicates a term of less than a day (likely overnight or very short-term deposits). M## represents the remaining months. This is important to understand the time horizon of the bank's liabilities.
REMAIN_TERM.domain: Valid values are 'D00' (less than a day) or 'M##' where ## represents the number of remaining months.  Months range from 01 to 36, though the distribution is skewed to shorter terms. Longer terms might indicate fixed deposits or loans.
REMAIN_TERM.constraints_description: Must be in the format 'D00' or 'M##' where ## is a two-digit number.  Values like 'M00' or 'M9' are invalid.  Check for unexpected values outside of the dominant categories.  Consider limiting the upper bound of months to a realistic value (e.g., 36 or 60).
REMAIN_TERM.relationships: The 'REMAIN_TERM' is likely related to the product type (e.g., fixed deposit vs. current account) and the origination date of the product. It may also indirectly impact the interest rate.
REMAIN_TERM.data_quality: Validate that the format is correct ('D00' or 'M##'). Ensure '##' is a valid two-digit number. Investigate unusual or unexpected values (e.g., large month values). Impute missing values using the mode ('D00') if appropriate, or based on related product characteristics.

WORKING_BALANCE.description: Working Balance: The account balance, including pending transactions. This represents the total funds accessible to the account holder, including transactions that have not yet been fully processed on the T24 core banking system. Crucial for assessing the bank's immediate liabilities.
WORKING_BALANCE.domain: Values range from 0 to 898,303,000,000 VND. Highly skewed to 0.  Represents the total balance, including uncleared transactions.  Should be non-negative.
WORKING_BALANCE.constraints_description: Must be a numeric value. Values should be non-negative. Monitor for extreme outliers that might indicate errors or fraudulent activity. Consider flagging accounts with balances exceeding a reasonable threshold (e.g., based on account type).
WORKING_BALANCE.relationships: Perfect positive correlation with ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL, ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL. Very high positive correlation with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
WORKING_BALANCE.data_quality: Validate that values are non-negative. Check for outliers and investigate anomalies. If there are significant differences with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL, further investigation of transaction history may be needed.

DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.description: Date of Last Credit Transaction: The date on which the customer last had a credit (incoming) transaction on their account. This provides insight into customer activity and engagement with the bank. A recent date indicates an active account.
DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.domain: Dates ranging from approximately 5 years ago to one year in the future (to account for potential scheduled future transactions). Represents the last incoming transaction. Should be a valid date.
DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.constraints_description: Must be a valid date in the format YYYY-MM-DD. Dates should fall within a reasonable historical range.  Future dates may be present, indicating scheduled credits.  Extremely old dates may indicate dormant accounts.
DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.relationships: Related to account activity, customer segment, and product type.  Likely correlated with DATE_LAST_DR_CUST (last debit transaction). A large gap between DATE_LAST_CR_CUST and DATE_LAST_DR_CUST may indicate inactivity.
DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.data_quality: Validate date format (YYYY-MM-DD). Check for dates outside the expected range. Impute missing values with caution; consider using a common date for inactive accounts or using a model based on customer segment and product type.

DATE_LAST_DR_CUST.description: Date of Last Debit Transaction: The date on which the customer last had a debit (outgoing) transaction on their account. This, combined with DATE_LAST_CR_CUST, provides a complete picture of customer account activity. High missing values may indicate accounts that have not been debited in a long time, potentially indicating savings accounts or dormant accounts.
DATE_LAST_DR_CUST.domain: Dates ranging from approximately 5 years ago to one year in the future (to account for potential scheduled future transactions). Represents the last outgoing transaction. Should be a valid date. High number of nulls expected for savings or dormant accounts.
DATE_LAST_DR_CUST.constraints_description: Must be a valid date in the format YYYY-MM-DD. Dates should fall within a reasonable historical range. Future dates may be present, indicating scheduled debits. A high percentage of null values is expected. When present, values should be within the same general timeframe as DATE_LAST_CR_CUST.
DATE_LAST_DR_CUST.relationships: Related to account activity, customer segment, and product type. Likely correlated with DATE_LAST_CR_CUST (last credit transaction). A large gap between DATE_LAST_CR_CUST and DATE_LAST_DR_CUST may indicate inactivity.
DATE_LAST_DR_CUST.data_quality: Validate date format (YYYY-MM-DD). Check for dates outside the expected range. Given the high number of missing values, consider creating a flag to indicate whether a debit transaction has occurred recently. Impute missing values with a special value or a model that accounts for account type and inactivity patterns.

DATE_LAST_CR_BANK.description: The date of the last credit transaction recorded by a bank for this customer.
DATE_LAST_CR_BANK.domain: Date values ranging from 2015-01-01 to today's date.  Represents the last credit transaction date at a bank.
DATE_LAST_CR_BANK.constraints_description: Valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Should generally be before today.
DATE_LAST_CR_BANK.relationships: Potentially related to other date fields like DATE_LAST_DR_BANK, DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO, DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.  May also relate to overall customer activity.
DATE_LAST_CR_BANK.data_quality: Check for format consistency (YYYY-MM-DD). Investigate dates in the future. High missing value percentage suggests this data is often unavailable. Consider imputing or handling missingness based on business context.

DATE_LAST_DR_BANK.description: The date of the last debit transaction recorded by a bank for this customer.
DATE_LAST_DR_BANK.domain: Date values ranging from 2015-01-01 to today's date. Represents the last debit transaction date at a bank.
DATE_LAST_DR_BANK.constraints_description: Valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Should generally be before today.
DATE_LAST_DR_BANK.relationships: Potentially related to other date fields like DATE_LAST_CR_BANK, DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO, DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO. May also relate to overall customer activity.
DATE_LAST_DR_BANK.data_quality: Check for format consistency (YYYY-MM-DD). Investigate dates in the future. Extremely high missing value percentage suggests this data is almost always unavailable.  May be best to exclude this column from analysis or use imputation very carefully.

DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.description: The date of the last credit transaction related to an automated process or service (e.g., loan payment, recurring billing).
DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.domain: Date values ranging from 2015-01-01 to today's date. Represents the last credit transaction date from an automated source.
DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.constraints_description: Valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Should generally be before today.
DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.relationships: Potentially related to other date fields like DATE_LAST_CR_BANK, DATE_LAST_DR_BANK, DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO. May indicate loan activity if payments are automated.
DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.data_quality: Check for format consistency (YYYY-MM-DD). Investigate dates in the future. Significant missing value percentage needs to be considered.

DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.description: The date of the last debit transaction related to an automated process or service (e.g., loan disbursement, direct debit).
DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.domain: Date values ranging from 2015-01-01 to today's date.  Represents the last debit transaction date from an automated source.
DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.constraints_description: Valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Should generally be before today.
DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.relationships: Potentially related to other date fields like DATE_LAST_CR_BANK, DATE_LAST_DR_BANK, DATE_LAST_CR_AUTO.  May indicate loan activity or recurring payments.
DATE_LAST_DR_AUTO.data_quality: Check for format consistency (YYYY-MM-DD). Investigate dates in the future. Extremely high missing value percentage suggests this data is almost always unavailable.  May be best to exclude this column from analysis or use imputation very carefully.

LIMIT_ID.description: Unique identifier for a credit limit assigned to a customer.
LIMIT_ID.domain: A numeric ID with a fixed suffix '.0009900.01'.  Represents a unique identifier for a credit limit.
LIMIT_ID.constraints_description: Should be a numeric value followed by the string '.0009900.01'.
LIMIT_ID.relationships: Potentially related to a credit limit amount column (if one exists).  May relate to customer segments or risk scores.
LIMIT_ID.data_quality: Check for consistency of the suffix '.0009900.01'.  Investigate duplicate IDs (though some duplication might be expected given the low unique count).  High missing value percentage suggests credit limits aren't consistently tracked.

LINE_NO.description: Line number or identifier. Represents a specific row or entry within the dataset.
LINE_NO.domain: Values from 3150 to 3350.  Acts as an internal identifier
LINE_NO.constraints_description: Must be a numeric value, generally between 3150 and 3350.
LINE_NO.relationships: Functionally dependent on REVAL_RATE, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, CURRENCY_SK. High correlation suggests a direct relationship with these other columns.
LINE_NO.data_quality: Check for data type consistency (should be numeric or convertible to numeric). Investigate the high null count and decide on appropriate handling (imputation or removal). Confirm functional dependency with mentioned columns.

CAMPAIGN_ID.description: Mã chương trình chiến dịch - Campaign identifier, a unique code for marketing campaigns.  Format is generally COMPANY.TYPE.DETAIL.
CAMPAIGN_ID.domain: Values starting with 'SEAB' or 'CBD', followed by campaign type and details.  Examples: 'SEAB.TG.TAILOC', 'CBD.2022.TG.PHATLOC'
CAMPAIGN_ID.constraints_description: Must adhere to a specific pattern: COMPANY.TYPE.DETAIL where COMPANY is 'SEAB' or 'CBD', TYPE is generally 'TG' or 'UUDAI', and DETAIL is alphanumeric.
CAMPAIGN_ID.relationships: No direct correlations listed, but the campaign likely influences account opening or deposit behavior.
CAMPAIGN_ID.data_quality: Validate against a list of active campaign codes or the defined pattern.  Address the high null count based on business requirements. Standardize campaign codes to ensure consistency.

SETLEMENT_AC.description: Tài khoản cắt tiền khi mở HĐ tiền gửi - Settlement Account: The account used to deduct funds when opening a deposit contract. May be VND account numbers or other internal identifiers.
SETLEMENT_AC.domain: Valid Vietnamese account numbers, or internal identifiers. Can start with 'VND' followed by digits, or consist of only digits.
SETLEMENT_AC.constraints_description: Must be a valid account number format for the bank (either a standard bank account number or an internal ID). Many of the entries will start with 'VND' followed by numbers.
SETLEMENT_AC.relationships: Relates to the customer's existing bank accounts. Likely tied to the CUSTOMER_SK.
SETLEMENT_AC.data_quality: Validate against the bank's account number format rules. Address the extremely high null count - indicates a data quality issue or that settlement accounts are often not recorded. Check for valid check-digit if possible.

CLOSE_REASON.description: Reason for account closure. This column is completely null, indicating that accounts are not closed in this dataset or the information is not available.
CLOSE_REASON.domain: Integer values representing different reasons for account closure. Values might be codes indicating reasons such as customer request, inactivity, fraud, etc.
CLOSE_REASON.constraints_description: Values must be valid integers, and should correspond to valid closure reason codes.  A separate lookup table would be needed to interpret these codes.
CLOSE_REASON.relationships: Relates to account status and balances. It's likely correlated with other columns indicating account activity. The listed 'functional_dependency' correlations seem erroneous given that the column contains all null values. This indicates either an error in the correlation analysis or a fundamental issue with the dataset.
CLOSE_REASON.data_quality: Investigate the 100% null count.  If data is missing, consider if the column is needed. If the values should not be null, investigate the source of the data and correct the issue.

TERM.description: Kỳ hạn mở - Opening Term: The term (duration) of the deposit account. Represented as 'M' followed by the number of months (e.g., M01 for 1 month, M12 for 12 months).
TERM.domain: Values 'M' followed by two digits representing months (e.g., M01, M06, M12, M24, M36).  Common values are M01, M03, M06, M12.
TERM.constraints_description: Must start with 'M' and be followed by a two-digit number between 01 and 36, representing months.  For example 'M06'.
TERM.relationships: Influences interest rates and account maturity dates. Related to PRODUCT_CODE if certain products have fixed terms.
TERM.data_quality: Validate that the value starts with 'M' and is followed by valid month numbers. Consider creating an enum of valid values (M01, M02, M03, etc.).

TERM_SBV.description: Kỳ hạn danh nghĩa của khoản tiền gửi, ví dụ: M01 (1 tháng), M06 (6 tháng), M12 (12 tháng).
TERM_SBV.domain: Khoảng thời gian gửi tiền, có thể là số tháng (Mxx) hoặc số ngày (Dxx).
TERM_SBV.constraints_description: Giá trị phải bắt đầu bằng 'M' theo sau là 2 chữ số (tháng) hoặc 'D' theo sau là 2 chữ số (ngày).
TERM_SBV.relationships: Có thể liên quan đến lãi suất và số tiền gửi, kỳ hạn càng dài, lãi suất có thể cao hơn.
TERM_SBV.data_quality: Kiểm tra tính hợp lệ của định dạng (Mxx hoặc Dxx). Kiểm tra xem kỳ hạn có hợp lý không (ví dụ: không có M00 hoặc D00).

ROLLOVER_TERM.description: Kỳ hạn tái tục tiền gửi, chỉ ra kỳ hạn được sử dụng khi tiền gửi được tự động gia hạn.
ROLLOVER_TERM.domain: Kỳ hạn tái tục thường là số tháng, ví dụ: 0001M (1 tháng), 0006M (6 tháng), 0012M (12 tháng).
ROLLOVER_TERM.constraints_description: Giá trị phải là một số có 1-4 chữ số, theo sau là 'M'.
ROLLOVER_TERM.relationships: Có thể liên quan đến kỳ hạn danh nghĩa (TERM_SBV). Nếu TERM_SBV là M01, ROLLOVER_TERM có thể là 0001M.
ROLLOVER_TERM.data_quality: Kiểm tra định dạng (sốM). Kiểm tra tính hợp lệ của kỳ hạn (ví dụ: không có 0000M). Xử lý giá trị null.

ORIG_INTEREST_RATE.description: Lãi suất ban đầu áp dụng cho khoản tiền gửi.
ORIG_INTEREST_RATE.domain: Lãi suất thường nằm trong khoảng từ 0% đến 12%.
ORIG_INTEREST_RATE.constraints_description: Giá trị phải là số thực không âm, thường có hai chữ số thập phân, và nằm trong khoảng 0-12.
ORIG_INTEREST_RATE.relationships: Tương quan cao với OFFER_RATE và FIRST_INTEREST. Kỳ hạn (TERM_SBV) có thể ảnh hưởng đến lãi suất.
ORIG_INTEREST_RATE.data_quality: Kiểm tra phạm vi giá trị (0-12). Xử lý giá trị null. Đảm bảo số chữ số thập phân hợp lý.

OFFER_RATE.description: Lãi suất chào bán, có thể khác với lãi suất ban đầu do các chương trình khuyến mãi hoặc điều kiện thị trường.
OFFER_RATE.domain: Lãi suất chào bán thường nằm trong khoảng 0% đến 9.5%.
OFFER_RATE.constraints_description: Giá trị phải là số thực không âm, thường có hai chữ số thập phân, và nằm trong khoảng 0-9.5.
OFFER_RATE.relationships: Tương quan cao với ORIG_INTEREST_RATE và FIRST_INTEREST.  Có thể liên quan đến chương trình khuyến mãi.
OFFER_RATE.data_quality: Kiểm tra phạm vi giá trị (0-9.5). Xử lý giá trị null. Đảm bảo số chữ số thập phân hợp lý.

FIRST_INTEREST.description: Lãi suất đầu tiên được áp dụng cho khoản tiền gửi, có thể là lãi suất khuyến mãi hoặc lãi suất cố định ban đầu.
FIRST_INTEREST.domain: Lãi suất thường nằm trong khoảng từ 0% đến 12%.
FIRST_INTEREST.constraints_description: Giá trị phải là số thực không âm, thường có hai chữ số thập phân, và nằm trong khoảng 0-12.
FIRST_INTEREST.relationships: Tương quan cao với ORIG_INTEREST_RATE và OFFER_RATE. Có thể liên quan đến loại tài khoản hoặc chương trình khuyến mãi.
FIRST_INTEREST.data_quality: Kiểm tra phạm vi giá trị (0-12). Xử lý giá trị null. Đảm bảo số chữ số thập phân hợp lý.

FIRST_BALANCE.description: Số dư đầu tiên của tài khoản. Represents the initial balance of the account.
FIRST_BALANCE.domain: Values should be non-negative integers representing the initial balance of an account, typically ranging from 0 to 10,000,000,000 VND.
FIRST_BALANCE.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Represented in VND.
FIRST_BALANCE.relationships: Highly correlated with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, suggesting dependency on account closure, loan origination system ID and transaction limit setup.
FIRST_BALANCE.data_quality: Validate that the value is a non-negative integer. Check for outliers that deviate significantly from the typical range (0-10,000,000,000 VND).

AGG_BAL_INTEREST.description: Tổng số dư sinh lãi. Represents the aggregated balance accruing interest.
AGG_BAL_INTEREST.domain: Values should be non-negative floating-point numbers representing the aggregated balance on which interest is calculated, typically ranging from 0 to 100,000,000,000 VND.
AGG_BAL_INTEREST.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Represented in VND. Precision to two decimal places is acceptable.
AGG_BAL_INTEREST.relationships: Highly correlated with TOT_INTEREST_AMT, CLOSE_REASON, INTEREST_BAL, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, indicating dependency on total interest amount, account closure, interest balance, loan origination system ID and transaction limit setup.
AGG_BAL_INTEREST.data_quality: Validate that the value is a non-negative number. Check for outliers that deviate significantly from the typical range (0-100,000,000,000 VND).  Handle null values appropriately.

INTEREST_BAL.description: Số dư lãi. Represents the interest balance of the account.
INTEREST_BAL.domain: Values should be non-negative numbers representing interest balance, with a significant number of zero values.  Typically ranging from 0 to 100,000,000 VND.
INTEREST_BAL.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Represented in VND. Expect a large proportion of zero values.  Consider capping at 100,000,000 VND.
INTEREST_BAL.relationships: Functionally dependent on TOT_INTEREST_AMT, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, indicating a strong relationship with total interest amount, account closure, loan origination system ID, and transaction limit setup.
INTEREST_BAL.data_quality: Validate that values are non-negative. Investigate accounts with unexpectedly high interest balances.  Handle null values appropriately.

SEAB_SALES_TYPE.description: Nhóm cán bộ bán (TELLER, CRO.IND...). Represents the sales type of the staff responsible for the account.
SEAB_SALES_TYPE.domain: Values should be one of the predefined sales types: TELLER, CRO.SME, RM, CRO.IND, VCRO, CRO.IND.HO.
SEAB_SALES_TYPE.constraints_description: Must be one of the following values: TELLER, CRO.SME, RM, CRO.IND, VCRO, CRO.IND.HO.
SEAB_SALES_TYPE.relationships: Potentially related to SEAB_SALES_ID, indicating the specific sales representative belonging to the sales type. No immediate functional dependencies are apparent from the provided correlations.
SEAB_SALES_TYPE.data_quality: Validate that the value belongs to the allowed set of sales types. Address null values based on business rules (e.g., assign to a default sales type).

SEAB_SALES_ID.description: ID của cán bộ bán. Represents the ID of the sales staff responsible for the account.
SEAB_SALES_ID.domain: Values should be integers representing the ID of the sales staff, typically ranging from 1,000,000 to 20,000,000. The IDs might have a structure or pattern specific to the bank.
SEAB_SALES_ID.constraints_description: Must be an integer.  Consider enforcing a range based on the bank's employee ID policies.
SEAB_SALES_ID.relationships: Strongly correlated with SEAB_BROKERS_ID, suggesting a relationship between sales staff and brokers. Functionally dependent on CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK, indicating a strong relationship with account closure, loan origination system ID and transaction limit setup.
SEAB_SALES_ID.data_quality: Validate that the value is an integer. Check for consistency with a table of valid employee IDs. Address null values based on business rules (e.g., assign a default or 'unknown' ID).

SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.description: Nhóm giới thiệu (NHANVIEN, DOITACLIENKET…). Specifies the type of entity that introduced the customer or transaction.
SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.constraints_description: Must be one of the predefined broker types.
SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.relationships: Related to SEAB_BROKERS_ID.  The ID should correspond to the type.  For example, if SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE is NHANVIEN, then SEAB_BROKERS_ID should be a valid employee ID.
SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.data_quality: Verify that the SEAB_BROKERS_ID corresponds to a valid entity based on the SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.  Check for misspellings or invalid values in the type field.

SEAB_BROKERS_ID.description: ID của bên giới thiệu. Unique identifier for the broker or entity that introduced the customer or transaction.
SEAB_BROKERS_ID.constraints_description: Must be a positive integer.  The ID should be valid within the context of the SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE.
SEAB_BROKERS_ID.relationships: Related to SEAB_BROKERS_TYPE. Functional dependencies with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK indicate a potential issue. These dependencies should be investigated to ensure data integrity.
SEAB_BROKERS_ID.data_quality: Validate against a list of valid broker IDs for each type. Check for consistency with the broker type.  Address the 100% correlations with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK as this is highly unlikely and needs investigation

TOTAL_LOCKED_AMT.description: Tổng số tiền phong tỏa đến ngày. Total amount of money locked (frozen) as of a specific date.
TOTAL_LOCKED_AMT.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative number. Should not exceed reasonable limits based on customer profile and account type.
TOTAL_LOCKED_AMT.relationships: High functional dependencies with TOT_INTEREST_AMT, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK. Investigate these dependencies as they may indicate data anomalies or redundant information.
TOTAL_LOCKED_AMT.data_quality: Check for negative values. Validate against known lock reason codes. Review outliers and ensure they are legitimate. Given the functional dependencies it's important to check for redundancy or errors causing those relationships.

SEAB_LOS_ID.description: Loan Origination System ID. Unique identifier for a loan application within the bank's loan origination system. This is likely a system-generated identifier.
SEAB_LOS_ID.constraints_description: Must be a positive integer. Follow a specific pattern, if applicable (e.g., length, prefix).
SEAB_LOS_ID.relationships: Has 100% functional dependencies on many other columns. This indicates it is either a synthetic key or there is severe data quality issue. Because of the complete nullness this column should likely be dropped.
SEAB_LOS_ID.data_quality: All values are null. This column is entirely missing, making it useless for analysis. It should be investigated to determine if data is truly missing, or is simply not being populated correctly during data extraction, or if this columns should be dropped completely.

AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.description: Account Transaction Limit Surrogate Key. A surrogate key representing the transaction limit associated with an account.  This is likely a foreign key to a table defining different transaction limit tiers.
AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.constraints_description: Must be one of the defined transaction limit keys. Should correspond to a valid record in the transaction limit table.
AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.relationships: Functional dependencies with TOT_INTEREST_AMT, CLOSE_REASON, and SEAB_LOS_ID. Investigate if these dependencies are valid within the data model.
AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.data_quality: Validate against the transaction limit table to ensure existence. Check for unexpected values. Review correlations.

CUSTOMER_SK.description: Mã SK (Surogate Key) theo chiều bản ghi customer tới bảng dim_ent_cust và dim_ent_cust_pii.  This is a surrogate key linking the transaction record to customer information. It provides a unique identifier for each customer.
CUSTOMER_SK.domain: Integer values representing customer identifiers, typically within a range of 8,000,000 to 30,500,000.
CUSTOMER_SK.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer.  Should be unique within the dataset and exist in the corresponding customer dimension table (dim_ent_cust, dim_ent_cust_pii).
CUSTOMER_SK.relationships: Foreign key referencing dim_ent_cust and dim_ent_cust_pii. Functional dependencies with CUSTOMER, CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK suggest these columns might be derived from the Customer Dimension table.
CUSTOMER_SK.data_quality: Validate that CUSTOMER_SK values are unique.  Verify that all CUSTOMER_SK values exist as primary keys in dim_ent_cust and dim_ent_cust_pii.  Monitor for sudden shifts in the distribution of CUSTOMER_SK values.

CATEGORY_SK.description: Mã SK (Surogate Key) theo chiều bản ghi customer tới bảng dim_ent_category.  This is a surrogate key that represents the category of the customer (e.g., individual, business).
CATEGORY_SK.domain: Integer values representing customer category identifiers, typically within a range of 100 to 7000.  The distribution shows a heavy concentration on a few key category IDs.
CATEGORY_SK.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should exist in the dim_ent_category table. Reflects a relatively small number of unique customer categories.
CATEGORY_SK.relationships: Foreign key referencing dim_ent_category.  Strong correlation with CATEGORY suggests a direct mapping. Functional dependencies with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK indicate a relationship within the customer dimension.
CATEGORY_SK.data_quality: Verify all CATEGORY_SK values exist as primary keys in dim_ent_category.  Monitor for large changes in the distribution of category IDs. Validate the relationship between CATEGORY_SK and CATEGORY.

PRODUCTS_SK.description: Mã Sk theo chiều sản phẩm tới bảng dim_ent_product. This surrogate key points to the product or service associated with the transaction.
PRODUCTS_SK.domain: Integer values representing product identifiers, typically within a range of 100,000 to 9,000,000.
PRODUCTS_SK.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should exist in the dim_ent_product table. Likely represents a limited set of products offered by the bank.
PRODUCTS_SK.relationships: Foreign key referencing dim_ent_product. Strong correlation with PRODUCT_CODE.  Functional dependencies with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
PRODUCTS_SK.data_quality: Verify all PRODUCTS_SK values exist as primary keys in dim_ent_product.  Validate the relationship between PRODUCTS_SK and PRODUCT_CODE.  Monitor for the introduction of new product IDs.

COMPANY_SK.description: Mã Sk theo chiều sản phẩm tới bảng dim_ent_company. This surrogate key identifies the company (if any) associated with the customer or transaction.
COMPANY_SK.domain: Integer values representing company identifiers, typically within a range of 1 to 8,000,000.
COMPANY_SK.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should exist in the dim_ent_company table. Represents a moderate number of companies.
COMPANY_SK.relationships: Foreign key referencing dim_ent_company. Functional dependencies with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK suggest this relates to customer and transaction dimensions.
COMPANY_SK.data_quality: Verify all COMPANY_SK values exist as primary keys in dim_ent_company. Monitor for significant changes in the distribution of COMPANY_SK values.

CURRENCY_SK.description: Mã SK theo chiều sản phẩm tới bảng dim_ent_currency. This surrogate key represents the currency used in the transaction. Likely tied to Vietnamese Dong (VND) predominantly.
CURRENCY_SK.domain: Integer values representing currency identifiers.  Virtually all transactions are likely in Vietnamese Dong (VND).
CURRENCY_SK.constraints_description: Must be a valid currency identifier. Should exist in the dim_ent_currency table. Primarily VND, with a very small possibility of another currency.
CURRENCY_SK.relationships: Foreign key referencing dim_ent_currency.  Strong correlation with REVAL_RATE. Functional dependencies with CLOSE_REASON, SEAB_LOS_ID, and AC_TRANS_LIMIT_SK.
CURRENCY_SK.data_quality: Verify all CURRENCY_SK values exist as primary keys in dim_ent_currency. Monitor the distribution of currency values, ensuring VND remains dominant.  Validate the relationship between CURRENCY_SK and REVAL_RATE.

CHANNEL_SK.description: Mã SK theo chiều sản phẩm tới bảng dim_ent_channel. This represents a foreign key linking to the channel dimension table. It indicates the distribution channel used for the financial transaction.
CHANNEL_SK.domain: Positive integer representing a channel identifier. Typical values range from 1 to 1000, but the actual range is defined by the dim_ent_channel table.
CHANNEL_SK.constraints_description: Must be a valid foreign key present in the dim_ent_channel table. Should be an integer.
CHANNEL_SK.relationships: Foreign key relationship to dim_ent_channel. Correlated to interest amount, close reason, and LOS ID.
CHANNEL_SK.data_quality: Verify that all CHANNEL_SK values exist in the dim_ent_channel table. Address missing values appropriately, possibly with an 'Unknown' channel.

CONTRACT_SK.description: Mã SK theo chiều hợp đồng chính tới bảng dim_ent_term_deposit. This uniquely identifies a contract within the term deposit system. It is a foreign key linking to the dim_ent_term_deposit table, where detailed contract information is stored.
CONTRACT_SK.domain: Unique integer identifier for a term deposit contract.  Ranges from 10000 to 35000 (example, may be different in reality)
CONTRACT_SK.constraints_description: Must be a unique integer and exist as a primary key in the dim_ent_term_deposit table.
CONTRACT_SK.relationships: This is the primary key for the term deposit contract and is functionally dependent on all other columns in the term deposit table. Foreign key relationships to various dimension tables.
CONTRACT_SK.data_quality: Ensure uniqueness and integrity with the dim_ent_term_deposit table. Verify referential integrity.

ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL.description: Số dư cuối ngày của TK trên T24, không bao gồm giao dịch forward. Represents the end-of-day balance of the account on the T24 system, excluding forward transactions.  Measured in the smallest currency unit (e.g., VND).
ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL.domain: A non-negative integer representing the account balance in VND (or other currency, depending on context). Reasonable values range from 0 to 1,000,000,000 VND.
ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should be consistent with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.
ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL.relationships: Strong positive correlation with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL. Related to close reason and interest balance.
ONLINE_ACTUAL_BAL.data_quality: Verify that the balance is non-negative. Compare with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL for consistency.  Investigate large values for potential outliers.

SUB_CHANNEL_ID.description: Kênh thực hiện giao dịch (sub). Specifies the sub-channel through which the transaction was conducted.  Examples include LOS (Loan Origination System) or SEAPORTAL (Self-service online portal).
SUB_CHANNEL_ID.domain: A string representing the sub-channel. Values include LOS, SEAPORTAL, MOBILE_APP, BRANCH, etc.
SUB_CHANNEL_ID.constraints_description: Must be a valid sub-channel code.  Consider defining a lookup table for valid values.
SUB_CHANNEL_ID.relationships: Related to CHANNEL_SK, providing more granular information about the transaction channel.
SUB_CHANNEL_ID.data_quality: Validate against a list of approved sub-channel codes. Address missing values, potentially with an 'Unknown' category.

FREQUENCY_DATE.description: Ngày nhận lãi hàng tháng (cùng mối liên hệ với trường DIM_DEPOSIT.FREQUENCY).  This represents the date on which interest is received monthly. It corresponds to the frequency setting in the DIM_DEPOSIT table.
FREQUENCY_DATE.domain: A date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. The day of the month should generally correspond to the frequency setting in the term deposit contract.
FREQUENCY_DATE.constraints_description: Must be a valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format. The day of the month should be a valid day. Should be consistent with the frequency setting in the associated DIM_DEPOSIT record.
FREQUENCY_DATE.relationships: Related to the FREQUENCY field in the DIM_DEPOSIT table. Influenced by contract terms and interest payment schedules.
FREQUENCY_DATE.data_quality: Verify that the date is valid and in the correct format.  Compare the day of the month to the term deposit contract's frequency setting. Validate against holiday schedules.

FAVORITE_TERM.description: Kỳ hạn yêu thích (là kỳ hạn thực tế KH mong muốn tất toán, VD KH gửi kỳ hạn 36 tháng nhưng muốn tất toán ở kỳ hạn 12 tháng và được hưởng lãi suất của 12 tháng). Represents the customer's preferred deposit term in months, even if different from the original agreement.
FAVORITE_TERM.domain: Integer representing the desired term in months, typically between 0 and 720 (60 years). 0 may represent immediate withdrawal.
FAVORITE_TERM.constraints_description: Must be a valid integer representing a month or a fraction of a month. Values should be non-negative. The presence of many null values suggests it's not always applicable.
FAVORITE_TERM.relationships: May correlate with the actual deposit term. A discrepancy would indicate the customer's desire to terminate the deposit earlier than originally agreed upon.
FAVORITE_TERM.data_quality: High percentage of null values suggest this field is optional. Validate to be either NULL or an integer within the specified range.  Check for outliers beyond a reasonable maximum term.

OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL.description: Số dư đầu ngày của TK trên T24. The account balance at the beginning of the day according to the T24 banking system.
OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL.domain: Non-negative integer representing the account balance in Vietnamese Dong (VND).  Values are typically between 0 and 900,000,000,000 (900 billion VND).
OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should not be negative. The values are balance in local currency (VND).
OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL.relationships: Strong positive correlation with ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL, indicating they represent balances at different points in time (beginning vs. end of day).  Functional dependency on several other columns suggests a fixed relationship based on those values.
OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL.data_quality: Validate that the value is a non-negative integer.  Check for consistency with ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL. Investigate cases where the difference between OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL and ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL is unusually large, as this might indicate suspicious activity or errors.

ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.description: Số dư cuối ngày của TK trên T24, bao gồm giao dịch forward. The account balance at the end of the day according to the T24 banking system, including forward transactions.
ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.domain: Non-negative integer representing the account balance in Vietnamese Dong (VND).  Values are typically between 0 and 900,000,000,000 (900 billion VND).
ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.constraints_description: Must be a non-negative integer. Should not be negative. The values are balance in local currency (VND).
ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.relationships: Strong positive correlation with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL. Functional dependency on several other columns suggests a fixed relationship based on those values.
ONLINE_CLEARED_BAL.data_quality: Validate that the value is a non-negative integer.  Check for consistency with OPEN_ACTUAL_BAL. Investigate large deviations from the opening balance.
